1. cs.HCI (Human-Computer Interaction) - The paper investigates user collaboration with conversational agents, which falls under the domain of HCI. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper compares the performance of two different chatbot systems, which involves the use of AI techniques. 
3. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - The paper deals with natural language processing and conversational agents, which are relevant topics in CL. 
4. cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity) - The paper may touch upon issues related to security and privacy in the context of user collaboration with digital assistants. 
5. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) - The paper may involve information retrieval techniques to enable the chatbots to provide financial advice to users.
